Articles.Content:
Ksp version 1.9.1

It started out when i recovered a vessel, I wasnt able to get back in the VAB, for some reason, then I decided to do some science on my space station by clicking on a vessel nearby the ksc that I had, and going in the map view and clicking on the space station, but the station was gone. I checked the persistant.sfs file and I saw my crew were still assigned on board, (and not dead) indicating that my station didn't explode. Then i decided to restart the game to fix the bug where i couldnt do anything at the ksc,  but then it decided to crash non stop after that.

Note: No new mods/new parts by ubiowelding were installed/made.

 

Here is the crash log

16 minutes ago, StocksAndStonks said:

 why not have zip folder in my gamedata or have 2 module managers?

Because these two conditions both indicate problems with installation.

First, you should only have the most recent version of module manager installed.  Having multiple versions leads to unpredictable behaviour.

Second, the contents of a zip file must be extracted before being placed into your gamedata folder.  The game has no capacity to unzip files itself.


Happy landings!
